					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">My responses to these questions got rather wordy and started to further depart from the original post on 8x8 attrs so I've decided to answer these questions in a separate <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=9&amp;t=17247" class="postlink">thread</a>.</div><br /><br />Haha, thanks for that. But it wouldn't be nesdev.com without the wildly offtopic tangents... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />Anyway, the questions I hoped to get some feedback on would be what various trade-offs people think are useful to get those mythical 8x8 attributes in a homebrew game...<br /><br />So, open questions:<br />* Do you even feel 8x8 attributes are worth the extra hassle, with the inconvenient memory layout and all?<br />* Which of the possible configurations would be your favorite? Conventional H/V mirroring trading away CHR tiles? One-screen mirroring leaving CHR alone? Or variants on the 4-screen configuration?<br />* How many extra $ would you be willing to spend on board replication to have 8x8 attributes in your game, before it starts to bite?</div>

